Hello,

To add a domain to your scope without making it a seed, you can add it to your (accepting) SurtPrefixedDecideRule. You&#39;ll find this block in the default config:

     &lt;!-- ...then ACCEPT those within configured/seed-implied SURT prefixes... --&gt;
     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.SurtPrefixedDecideRule&quot;&gt;
      &lt;!-- &lt;property name=&quot;seedsAsSurtPrefixes&quot; value=&quot;true&quot; /&gt; --&gt;
      &lt;!-- &lt;property name=&quot;alsoCheckVia&quot; value=&quot;false&quot; /&gt; --&gt;
      &lt;!-- &lt;property name=&quot;surtsSourceFile&quot; value=&quot;&quot; /&gt; --&gt;
      &lt;!-- &lt;property name=&quot;surtsDumpFile&quot; value=&quot;${launchId}/surts.dump&quot; /&gt; --&gt;
      &lt;!-- &lt;property name=&quot;surtsSource&quot;&gt;
            &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.spring.ConfigString&quot;&gt;
             &lt;property name=&quot;value&quot;&gt;
              &lt;value&gt;
               # example.com
               # http://www.example.edu/path1/
               # +http://(org,example,
              &lt;/value&gt;
             &lt;/property&gt;
            &lt;/bean&gt;
           &lt;/property&gt; --&gt;
     &lt;/bean&gt;

Uncomment the surtsSource and list your domains in the &lt;value&gt; section.

Oh, you&#39;re asking about 1.14.x... same idea except:

           &lt;newObject name=&quot;acceptIfSurtPrefixed&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.crawler.deciderules.SurtPrefixedDecideRule&quot;&gt;
             &lt;string name=&quot;decision&quot;&gt;ACCEPT&lt;/string&gt;
             &lt;string name=&quot;surts-source-file&quot;&gt;&lt;/string&gt;
             &lt;boolean name=&quot;seeds-as-surt-prefixes&quot;&gt;true&lt;/boolean&gt;
             &lt;string name=&quot;surts-dump-file&quot;&gt;&lt;/string&gt;
           &lt;/newObject&gt;

Set the value of surts-source-file (our convention is &quot;surts.txt&quot;) and list your domains in that file.

Noah


